Suspected al Shabaab militants early today attacked a police post at Pandanguo in Lamu West.Pandanguo headman Adan Golja said villagers fled after gunshots were heard at the post at around 5.30am.A senior police officer confirmed the incident adding that security officers were deployed to the scene.He said they are yet to establish if there are casualties or officers injured following the attack.The attackers also reportedly destroyed a communication mast in the village.County police commander Muchangi Kioi said he is not aware of the attack but would follow up the matter.More to follow